						               													<description>Bluff, attack, take risks in flash games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a ship, every pirate has his place. Recruit your crew by avoiding mutiny. A pair of pirates, and it&amp;rsquo;s lost!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The number shown on a card corresponds to the number of its copies in the package, namely one card, two cards 2 and ten cards 10. With this strong principle, it is possible to evaluate the remaining cards in the pickaxe, and thus to take risks and make the right decision.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To begin, each player receives three cards, and at the same time, each one slams a card in front of him. The smallest value begins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turn, one of the following actions can be taken:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Draw a card and keep it in your hand&amp;#10;     Attack a player: lay a card with his hand in front of a player, of a value other than those already in front of the player (he cannot be paired)&amp;#10;     Accuse a player if you think he has a pair in his hand (or between the cards in front of him and his hand). If he does, he&amp;rsquo;s eliminated, otherwise it is you.&amp;#10;     Challenge a player: draw a card without looking at it and shoot it in front of a player. If you form a pair with a card already present, YOU are eliminated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
